public enum SpawnSearch
extends java.lang.Enum<SpawnSearch>

Specifies directions a LocalAreaGate will search for a spawn location when a player arrives.

When a player teleports to a LocalAreaGate, the gates randomly picks a location within the volume defined between its two corners. It then adjusts the y-coordinate (vertical) based on the gate options that allow or disallow spawning into solid or liquid blocks. This enumeration specifies how the gate will search for a suitable spawn location.
